abstract:
The first observation of the semileptonic $b$-baryon decay $ \Lambda_b^0 ightarrow \Lambda_c^+ 	au^-\overline{
u}_{	au}$, with a significance of $6.1\,\sigma$, is reported using a data sample corresponding to 3 fb$^{-1}$ of integrated luminosity, collected by the LHCb experiment at centre-of-mass energies of 7 and 8 TeV at the LHC. The $	au^-$ lepton is reconstructed in the hadronic decay to three charged pions. The branching fraction ${\mathcal{B}}(\Lambda_b^0 ightarrow \Lambda_c^+	au^-\overline{
u}_{	au}) = (1.50 \pm 0.16\pm 0.25\pm 0.23)\%$ is obtained, where uncertainties are statistical, systematic and from the external branching fraction of the normalisation channel $\Lambda_b^0ightarrow \Lambda_c^+\pi^-\pi^+\pi^-$. The ratio of semileptonic branching fractions ${\mathcal{R}}( \Lambda_c^+)\equiv {\mathcal{B}}( \Lambda_b^0 ightarrow \Lambda_c^+ 	au^-\overline{
u}_{	au})/{\mathcal{B}}( \Lambda_b^0 ightarrow \Lambda_c^+ \mu^-\overline{
u}_{\mu})$ is derived to be $0.242 \pm 0.026 \pm 0.040\pm 0.059$, where the external branching fraction uncertainty from the channel $\Lambda_b^0ightarrow \Lambda_c^+\mu^-\overline{
u}_{\mu}$ contributes to the last term. This result is in agreement with the Standard Model prediction.

